      "sc:description": "abnum is a web tool developed by Prof. Andrew C.R. Martin's group at UCL that automatically numbers antibody sequences or structures using the Kabat, Chothia, or Martin schemes. It facilitates antibody engineering by ensuring accurate numbering.",
